otal gain), as is common for Section 1256 contracts under the U.S. tax code.", "impact_scope": "output_interpretation"}], "inputs": [{"name": "purchase_value", "type": "number", "required": true, "description": "The initial purchase price of the contract.", "unit": null, "aliases": []}, {"name": "end_of_year_value", "type": "number", "required": true, "description": "The fair market value of the contract at the end of the tax year, used for mark-to-market accounting.", "unit": null, "aliases": []}, {"name": "sale_value", "type": "number", "required": true, "description": "The value for which the contract is sold subsequent to year-end.", "unit": null, "aliases": []}], "output": {"name": "total_long_term_gain", "type": "number", "unit": "dollars", "description": "The total long-term capital gain realized from both the year-end mark-to-market valuation and the subsequent sale of the contract, after applying the 60% long-term tax rule."}, "execution": {"language": "python", "entrypoint": "compute", "code": "def compute(inputs):\n    purchase_value = inputs['purchase_value']\n    end_of_year_value = inputs['end_of_year_value']\n    sale_value = inputs['sale_value']\n    year_end_gain = end_of_year_value - purchase_value\n    year_end_long_term = year_end_gain * 0.6\n    sale_gain = sale_value - end_of_year_value\n    sale_long_term = sale_gain * 0.6\n    total_long_term_gain = year_end_long_term + sale_long_term\n    return round(total_long_term_gain)", "deterministic": true}, "diagnostic_checks": [{"rule_id": "dr001", "name": "Positive Purchase Value", "check_type": "deterministic", "diagnostic_type": "E", "severity": "error", "predicate_mode": "violation", "expression": "inputs['purchase_value'] <= 0", "applies_to": ["purchase_value"], "description": "The initial purchase value of a contract must be a positive number."}, {"rule_id": "dr002", "name": "Non-Negative End-of-Year Value", "check_type": "deterministic", "diagnostic_type": "E", "severity": "alert", "predicate