t of debt (as a decimal, e.g., 0.04 for 4%). Note: The function's internal calculation applies a tax shield to this value.", "unit": null, "aliases": []}, {"name": "equity_value", "type": "number", "required": true, "description": "The market value of the company's equity.", "unit": null, "aliases": []}, {"name": "debt_value", "type": "number", "required": true, "description": "The market value of the company's debt.", "unit": null, "aliases": []}, {"name": "tax_rate", "type": "number", "required": true, "description": "The corporate tax rate applicable to the company (as a decimal, e.g., 0.25 for 25%).", "unit": null, "aliases": []}], "output": {"name": "wacc", "type": "number", "unit": "decimal", "description": "The Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC) as a decimal."}, "execution": {"language": "python", "entrypoint": "compute", "code": "def compute(inputs):\n    equity_cost = inputs['equity_cost']\n    debt_cost = inputs['debt_cost']\n    equity_value = inputs['equity_value']\n    debt_value = inputs['debt_value']\n    tax_rate = inputs['tax_rate']\n    total_value = equity_value + debt_value\n    wacc = equity_value / total_value * equity_cost + debt_value / total_value * debt_cost * (1 - tax_rate)\n    return wacc", "deterministic": true}, "diagnostic_checks": [{"rule_id": "wacc_cost_non_negative", "name": "Non-negative Costs and Tax Rate", "check_type": "deterministic", "diagnostic_type": "E", "severity": "error", "predicate_mode": "violation", "expression": "inputs['equity_cost'] < 0 or inputs['debt_cost'] < 0 or inputs['tax_rate'] < 0", "applies_to": [], "description": "Cost of equity, cost of debt, and tax rate should not be negative as they represent economic costs or government levies."}, {"rule_id": "wacc_value_non_negative", "name": "Non-negative Market Values", "check_type": "deterministic", "diagnostic_type": "E", "severity": "error", "predicate_mode": "violation", "expression": "inputs['equity_value'] < 0 or inputs['debt_value'] < 0", "applies_to"