ar bond, expressed as a decimal (e.g., 0.18 for 18%).", "unit": null, "aliases": []}], "output": {"name": "future_one_year_rate", "type": "number", "unit": "decimal", "description": "The forecasted interest rate for the one-year bond in the next year, expressed as a decimal."}, "execution": {"language": "python", "entrypoint": "compute", "code": "def compute(inputs):\n    two_year_rate = inputs['two_year_rate']\n    current_one_year_rate = inputs['current_one_year_rate']\n    compounded_two_year_factor = (1 + two_year_rate) ** 2\n    future_one_year_factor = compounded_two_year_factor / (1 + current_one_year_rate)\n    future_one_year_rate = future_one_year_factor - 1\n    return future_one_year_rate", "deterministic": true}, "diagnostic_checks": [{"rule_id": "input_two_year_rate_type", "name": "Two-year rate must be numeric", "check_type": "normalization", "diagnostic_type": "F", "severity": "error", "predicate_mode": "validity", "expression": "isinstance(inputs.get('two_year_rate'), (int, float))", "applies_to": ["two_year_rate"], "description": "The 'two_year_rate' input must be a numeric value (integer or float)."}, {"rule_id": "input_current_one_year_rate_type", "name": "Current one-year rate must be numeric", "check_type": "normalization", "diagnostic_type": "F", "severity": "error", "predicate_mode": "validity", "expression": "isinstance(inputs.get('current_one_year_rate'), (int, float))", "applies_to": ["current_one_year_rate"], "description": "The 'current_one_year_rate' input must be a numeric value (integer or float)."}, {"rule_id": "two_year_rate_non_negative", "name": "Two-year rate must be non-negative", "check_type": "deterministic", "diagnostic_type": "E", "severity": "error", "predicate_mode": "violation", "expression": "inputs['two_year_rate'] < 0", "applies_to": ["two_year_rate"], "description": "The two-year bond interest rate cannot be negative in this context."}, {"rule_id": "current_one_year_rate_non_negative", "name": "Current one-year rate m