st of tax rates corresponding to each tax bracket. The length of this list should be one greater than the number of tax brackets, with the last rate applying to income above the highest bracket.", "unit": null, "aliases": ["marginal_rates"]}], "output": {"name": "tax_liability", "type": "number", "unit": "dollars", "description": "The total tax amount owed based on the progressive tax system."}, "execution": {"language": "python", "entrypoint": "compute", "code": "def compute(inputs):\n    taxable_income = inputs['taxable_income']\n    tax_brackets = inputs['tax_brackets']\n    tax_rates = inputs['tax_rates']\n    tax_liability = 0.0\n    for i, rate in enumerate(tax_rates):\n        lower_bound = 0 if i == 0 else tax_brackets[i - 1]\n        upper_bound = tax_brackets[i] if i < len(tax_brackets) else float('inf')\n        if taxable_income > lower_bound:\n            amount_to_tax_in_current_bracket = min(taxable_income, upper_bound) - lower_bound\n            tax_liability += amount_to_tax_in_current_bracket * rate\n    return round(tax_liability)", "deterministic": true}, "diagnostic_checks": [{"rule_id": "ti_001", "name": "Non-negative taxable income", "check_type": "deterministic", "diagnostic_type": "E", "severity": "error", "predicate_mode": "violation", "expression": "inputs['taxable_income'] < 0", "applies_to": [], "description": "Taxable income cannot be negative."}, {"rule_id": "tl_001", "name": "Tax brackets and rates length consistency", "check_type": "deterministic", "diagnostic_type": "F", "severity": "error", "predicate_mode": "validity", "expression": "len(inputs['tax_rates']) == len(inputs['tax_brackets']) + 1", "applies_to": [], "description": "For a progressive tax system, the number of tax rates must be exactly one more than the number of tax brackets (e.g., [bracket1, bracket2] -> [rate1, rate2, rate3])."}, {"rule_id": "tb_001", "name": "Valid tax brackets structure and order", "check_type": "deterministic", "diagnostic_type": "E", "severity": 